Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.43,0:00:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we're going to discuss um how\Nto live your life like a prayer. Um we
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.88,0:00:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,have done other uh one lecture about it.\NUm but I there were some things that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.40,0:00:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,were missing and I wanted to touch on\Ncertain um
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.76,0:00:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics that of prayer. So um my\Nfirst question is when you say live your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.03,0:00:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,life like a prayer\Nuh what is your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.92,0:00:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,interpretation of that? It means to to\Ndedicate your uh life to lovingness and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the acknowledgment of the divinity of\Nour creator
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.28,0:00:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh to love your fellow man as\Nyourself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:01:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be willing to forgive\Nuh any seeming shortcomings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.96,0:01:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh to forgive the past especially\Nbecause if you think of it every
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.88,0:01:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,resentment that you have or anger or\Ndismay or something is always about the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.08,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,past.\NPeople never realize it. Every negative
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.00,0:01:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling you have is about the past.\NWhatever you're upset about happened
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.43,0:01:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,already and it's over.\NSo the big news is get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.24,0:01:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if somebody shot your foot off,\Nthat was just a few seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.15,0:01:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not now. It was already the past.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.88,0:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,stop clinging to the past\Nallows us a much greater freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.20,0:01:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,uh to be who we really are and to\Ndiscover the presence of God as as
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.84,0:02:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness within us.\NSo we by letting go of the past we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.96,0:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,uh give dominion to the lovingness which\Nit prevails in the present which is the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic of the presence of God.\NSo we acknowledge God's presence by our
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.28,0:02:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness to let go of the past and to\Nbe loving and receptive in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So should we live in the present? You\Ndon't have any choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.28,0:02:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You live in the present whether you like\Nit or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.95,0:02:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you know, as far as the reality of the\Nphysicality goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Psychologically, many people cling to\Nthe past.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.08,0:02:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know lots of people that haven't grown\Nup since they were maybe 12 or 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.64,0:02:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, the new book that we have written\Nis about letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.\N>> of um resentments and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,um different\Nu positionalities that we have about who
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.72,0:03:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we are and what we are.\N>> Yes. Those are all all remnants of the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.20,0:03:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,past.\N>> Mhm. our definition of our self
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.44,0:03:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and our emotional opinions about\Neverything up to the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.80,0:03:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of seconds ago\Nare are all belong to the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um\N>> what I just said is already in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.20,0:03:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even care about it now.\N>> So So when you pray
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.12,0:03:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and um how should you pray?\NWell, you can't tell people how to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's it's an attitude. Prayer to me is a\Nreverential attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:04:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And um because it's an attitude, it can\Nprevail anywhere, anytime, any place in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.15,0:04:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,an airplane and in Alaska or wherever it\Nmay be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.12,0:04:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The same reverence for life,\Nthe awareness that divinity is the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.76,0:04:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,source of this life\Nand the reverence for that divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.40,0:04:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,prevails over all else.\NWhat I said is already the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um\Nfor instance um when you pray uh you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.88,0:04:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,have often said don't do not outline.\N>> Yes. So what do you mean outline?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.32,0:04:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What that means is not to tell God how\Nto do a thing or what his business is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.24,0:04:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Npeople try to tell God what you know
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.63,0:04:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what they need when they need it and\Nwith whom and under what circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh that of course limits uh that\Nlimits everything. So when we say I ask
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.68,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,God for knowledge of his will for me and\Nthe power to carry that out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a very common prayer. I ask for\NGod's will for me and the power to carry
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.36,0:05:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that out. And you do that one day at a\Ntime every morning. I pray for knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.24,0:05:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of your will for me this Lord this day\Nthis Lord and ask for the power to carry
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.75,0:05:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it out.\NAnd that's a very common prayer. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,common to all the 12step groups. They\Nall follow the same 12 steps. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.75,0:05:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. Um\NI'm trying to think of a example. Um
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.75,0:05:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when you pray and you say, "Well, let's\Njust do this." All right. I want to win
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.19,0:05:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the lottery. Now, you know as well as I\Ndo that a lot of people that win the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.60,0:06:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,lottery are miserable,\Nbut um you know a lot of people think
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.40,0:06:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that money is going to solve all their\Nproblems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.16,0:06:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's just expressing a wish. That's\Nnot really prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.19,0:06:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Okay. Prayer would be uh where you ask
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.19,0:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God to make sure that you win the\Nlottery. Asking God to vote in your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.00,0:06:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,favor. Mhm.\N>> Uh so that's a different kind of a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.91,0:06:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,opinion to have about God\N>> and your expectations of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\NI was brought up to to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,everything to God as as surrender\Neverything to God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.75,0:06:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Express your wishes and then surrender\Nthem to God's will. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.72,0:06:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And if you were meant to be rich and\Nfamous, you will be and if you weren't,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.19,0:06:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't.\NSo it's sort of an implication of karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.36,0:06:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,propensities in a way.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:07:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Which is not a common common\Nuh notion in Christianity karma that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.12,0:07:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,arises more in the eastern religions\Nthat we don't speak about Christian
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.91,0:07:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,karma.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.56,0:07:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when is prayer useful? I mean they've\Ndone all kind of studies about people
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who are ill and um if they were had a\Ngroup of people praying for them that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.31,0:07:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they recovered quicker than other people\Nwho are not who
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. There's been sort of a scientific\Ndocumentation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.88,0:07:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of the beneficial effects of prayer\N>> by oneself and others and hopefully by
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.03,0:07:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,both oneself and others.\NSo that prayer has been scientifically
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.80,0:07:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,documented to be of benefit.\NAnd what if it wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you stop praying, right?\NSo, it's beneficial to have these prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,lists or pray for people that um are\Ngoing through times of challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,health-wise. And\N>> I I think so definitely because uh not
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.47,0:08:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,only for their benefit, but actually for\Nyour own even if their life doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.19,0:08:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,improve, you've appealed to God uh uh to\Nassist you in the human condition. So it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.00,0:08:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly has affected your own life\N>> and then hopefully also the life of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,others.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.15,0:08:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. What about um for instance we\Nalways bless our food before we consume
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it. So what is can you give me an why we\Ndo that? Why do we bless our food before
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.88,0:08:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we eat it? Does it change it that?\N>> Well, we bless it because uh of thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:09:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for one thing that we have enough to\Neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Many people in the world do not have\Nenough to eat. So, I give thanks to the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.27,0:09:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord for this wonderful meal and it's an\Nexpression of God's love that I my needs
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.51,0:09:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,are provided for.\NSo I express my gratitude, my
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.08,0:09:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thankfulness\Nand u that completes the circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.80,0:09:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.12,0:09:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you say would be a useful\Nprayer? I mean when would you use prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to in helping others?\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.36,0:09:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> well I think in a way\Nuh prayer is useful all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.24,0:09:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Um there is an admonition\Npray constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.32,0:09:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you pray for yourself. You pray for\Nothers. You pray for the human
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.00,0:10:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,condition.\NYou pray for little little animals who
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.00,0:10:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,depend on you for their life.\NYou pray for the ones you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.83,0:10:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the meantime, you thank God for\Nall of the above.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.72,0:10:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay?\N>> So I thank God that you are sitting next
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.16,0:10:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to me and giving me these questions to\Npuzzle with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.00,0:10:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when we have obstacles, would it\Nbe appropriate to um either see the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.83,0:10:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,obstacles to pray uh to see the\Nobstacles differently or do we pray to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.12,0:10:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,learn from those obstacles?\N>> Well, it depends uh how sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.51,0:10:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is praying.\N>> Well, we're trying to get better. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.92,0:10:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,why I want I want you to specify this. I\Nmean, I'm trying to get better at my
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.39,0:10:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,prayer\Nbecause, you know, it's I mean, more
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sophisticated.\N>> Well, you can see that the prayer is a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.00,0:11:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,personal thing of yourself.\NIt also implies that divinity is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,listening and capable of respond\Nresponding. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.39,0:11:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You include your environment and all the\Npeople and that you love
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the well-being of the world and\Nall of life within that world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.27,0:11:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mhm.\N>> Well, there's been research that says
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.24,0:11:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that I think it's is it the Japanese man\Nthat did that whole book study on uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.83,0:11:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,water and you pray over it and it\Nchanges
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, it changes the surface tension. Yes.\N>> It changes the actual
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,structure of the water.\N>> Yeah. So, I'm not familiar with that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.48,0:12:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,study, although I've heard of it. Yes.\NMhm. And so it prayer obviously is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.16,0:12:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,capable of doing marvelous things.\N>> Well, of course the the mind wants it to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.44,0:12:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,be proven,\N>> right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.51,0:12:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And faith doesn't require that it be\Nproven.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.16,0:12:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nwhether it can be proven that God
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.68,0:12:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,responds to my prayers or not, you know,\Nis irrelevant to me because I'm um
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.04,0:12:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting my view of myself and\Ndivinity and my relationship to divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh I'm not responsible for the\Nresults.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only uh responsible for my own\Nattitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thank God for everything in advance\Nand whether there's a response or not is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,actually quite irrelevant. Yeah.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.27,0:13:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, you you you pray to get to\Nschool on time and then you and then you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,know you know that old joke the kids\Nprays that he's late for school. play p
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.76,0:13:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,prays to God to help me get to school on\Ntime. And then he gets to the curb and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.56,0:13:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he trips and he says, "But I didn't ask\Nyou to push me."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I hadn't heard that one. That's good.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't ask you to push me.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,um, when you pray a lot of times, I\Nmean, I find that my prayers are usually
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.56,0:13:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for other people a lot of the time,\N>> for the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> For other people, you know.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.83,0:13:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um, and so\Nis it pro appropriate to ask prayers for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.51,0:13:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself?\N>> Well, I think so. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.95,0:13:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I mean, if you're all alone out in the\Nwoods, who else is going to pray for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.16,0:14:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you?\NYou could say, "Dear God, I'm lost in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.24,0:14:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,these woods.\NDon't know where I am. I've lost my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.16,0:14:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,compass\Nand the animals have run off with my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.24,0:14:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,food.\NIt's just you and God."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, could be God's way of telling you\Nthis is your last day on Earth. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.04,0:14:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> so so when you outline\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.39,0:14:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is that saying that you want this\Noutcome because you're praying to God?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.76,0:14:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The outline is, you know, like telling\NGod his business
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.44,0:14:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,like uh you need that so much money and\Nyou need it by Monday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.56,0:14:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Outlining is telling God how how to how\Nto provide for you according to your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.04,0:14:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,will\N>> instead of asking for God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.95,0:15:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So your your will may be to get it and\Nhis will may be that you don't get it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.27,0:15:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,right.\N>> If you get more rich or more famous,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be in worse shape than\Nyou are already. So
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.68,0:15:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody wants to be rich and famous.\N>> Of course it's deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.24,0:15:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The daily news will tell you how how\Nmuch good it does you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.88,0:15:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nbut again that all depends on personal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.56,0:15:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,car. You can't say it's due to success\Nand fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people it benefits them\Ntremendously
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and other people it sort of ends their\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, like some people do good with what\Nthey have.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> They do accumulate.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.56,0:15:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Accumulated. They do all types of\Nwonderful things for people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:16:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> They really do.\N>> And there's other people that would not
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.24,0:16:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,do that if they had it.\N>> So, in some cases, it's beneficial. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.27,0:16:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> In other cases, it it brings their life\Nto an end almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.04,0:16:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> Get hooked up on fame and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, is the ego a little bit in there?\NYou know, when you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.39,0:16:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> more than a little bit, it's all there.\NMoney and fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.04,0:16:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I was trying to be nice.\NThat's the old Zen in there, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right?\N>> Just give me a little money in fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Like a million or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.95,0:16:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\NTo a lot of people, a million or two
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.56,0:17:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a small change,\N>> right? I knew people back in the east
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.80,0:17:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they would consider that small change\N>> but also you know I mean
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.88,0:17:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you've also talked about karma and how\Nkarmically you have to earn that quality
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.40,0:17:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,too\N>> that's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.79,0:17:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not a familiar concept in the west of\Nkarma
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.72,0:17:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right\N>> but karmically you have to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,handle it because a lot of people when\Nthey hit the lottery they just can't
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.84,0:17:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,handle any of that.\N>> Yes. It said routinely destroys people,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right?\N>> Uh the unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.67,0:17:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> And uh
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.88,0:17:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they just go under very fast.\N>> Yes. The history of people who win the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.32,0:17:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lottery\Nis pretty grim,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.20,0:17:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right?\N>> High divorce, high suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,alcohol and drugs.\N>> Their family quit talking to them. You
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.03,0:18:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,know, there's lots of I mean, I know a\Nfew. There's lots of them that their
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,family, you know, they no longer will\Ntalk to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.40,0:18:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, yes.\N>> They, you know, because they they want
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.20,0:18:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,money from them and\N>> Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.76,0:18:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You need to help all of us and because\Nwe're family and,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you know, so there's a lot of things\Nthat go are attached to it that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.08,0:18:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> the little greeneyed monster\N>> and I don't think other people realize
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.52,0:18:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that until they\N>> are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The greeneyed monster. Mhm.\N>> Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.91,0:18:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. So prayer is useful in our\Neveryday lives and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to\Nuse it in our everyday lives. Let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.36,0:18:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that we we're going to do a whole day in\Nour life. So we start off with prayer in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.08,0:18:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the morning asking God to give us a\Nwonderful day. Or what do we say when we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.44,0:19:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,start off in the morning?\N>> Well, we dedicate this day that I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,service, oh Lord, and I ask how I can be\Nbeneficial
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.36,0:19:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh to your\Nintention for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.48,0:19:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I I try to serve God and I try to serve\Nmy fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.52,0:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And by serving my fellow man, I serve\NGod. God doesn't need my service.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.00,0:19:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm very cooperative with God.\N>> And then we pray over our food and bless
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.03,0:19:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it. You know,\N>> we acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.24,0:19:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we acknowledge the sovereignty of\Ndivinity. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.91,0:19:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I mean, we don't have to make a big\Nproduction over it. You can say it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,silently before you eat. And\N>> that's what you can do. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You don't have to do a big production\Nout of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes, that's correct. Yes.\NMhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.08,0:19:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Especially in public places, you know,\Nand I Well, I've always felt that prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.88,0:20:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,was more personal on a personal level,\N>> you know, and that was my communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.52,0:20:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> You know, with a a a special higher
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.00,0:20:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,being.\N>> So, I always took it to more of a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.72,0:20:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,personal level level than a public.\N>> Yes. Yes. It's sort of a family feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.64,0:20:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to it,\N>> right? As dinner is served, you all uh
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.67,0:20:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thank give thanks for this meal and\N>> bless it in God's name
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.60,0:20:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with gratitude.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.32,0:20:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, you live life one day at a\Ntime. Uh grateful for God's gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the benefits that your life can have\Nin others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.48,0:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, what would you say to someone who\Ndoesn't believe in God or prayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.48,0:20:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say um\Num not to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.48,0:20:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. That's I mean there's plenty of\Npeople out there in in structured
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.91,0:21:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,religions that would not agree with you,\Nbut
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.96,0:21:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well,\Nthe faster trail to God is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.84,0:21:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,theoretically through prayer and\Ndivi divine service. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.36,0:21:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But also the miraculous occurs out out\Nof unexpectedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.91,0:21:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> And um I've seen people go from atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.76,0:21:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to a profound believer in a matter of\Nseconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.00,0:21:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wham. and all of a sudden you're hit by\Na bolt of lightning and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.64,0:21:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,during World War II. I remember that for\Ninstance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.96,0:21:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,guys and atheists but as the kamicazi\Npilots came down and the bullets started
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.28,0:21:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,flying they suddenly found God.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.55,0:21:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you've off often said that, you\Nknow, to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.72,0:22:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Ngo to the bullets
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.28,0:22:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,uh knowing the outcome\Nis a very high uh state.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.12,0:22:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That is a state of uh surrender.\NAnd in that particular culture, the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.40,0:22:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity includes uh\Nwhat we would call more the governmental
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.40,0:22:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh power structure.\NSo in that particular
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.72,0:22:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nsociety I respected their devotion to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.44,0:22:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God and their willingness to surrender\Ntheir life
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.28,0:22:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> to the good of their country which they\Nunderstood to be the way to serve God.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.52,0:22:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It also made them very dangerous\Nbecause if they're doing it for God, you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.84,0:22:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,know, they're willing to take any risk,\Nincluding taking your life with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.52,0:23:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> So,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I respected their devotion and their\Nbelief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.20,0:23:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is there any um repercussion for taking\Nanother human being's life? I mean, do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.32,0:23:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you can you answer that question or am I\Nasking something that I shouldn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.12,0:23:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, that that could take the next hour\Nto answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.64,0:23:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's what I thought.\NThat's what I thought. I mean, what are
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.36,0:23:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the, you know, karma is in that?\N>> Well, you have the overall uh context.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.91,0:23:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> And then you have the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have the person's capability\Nfor comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.72,0:23:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And then you have the duty in there. If\Nyou're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.28,0:23:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and then if you're in the service,\Nyou've got a duty. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.96,0:23:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So what are the complications?\N>> Obligation to your obligation to your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.03,0:23:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,fellow man.\N>> So there's several it's it's layered
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.12,0:23:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then the complications are layered in\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.32,0:24:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> multiplicities. Uhuh. Layer upon layer.\NYou do a thing out of devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.20,0:24:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That means you believe in God. And uh so\Nthat depends on your background and your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.03,0:24:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,background may prelude such kind of\Nattitudes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.36,0:24:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or it may require it. So it depends on\Nthe culture in which you grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.27,0:24:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Depends on the culture\N>> because many times you know people say
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.12,0:24:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,well you know what kind of person would\Ntake another person's life and it weighs
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.36,0:24:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,very heavily on our servicemen.\NIndeed it does
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.44,0:24:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> that they you know because I hear so\Nmany times you know you being in the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.12,0:24:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,service uh say I'm so glad I did not\Nhave to kill someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.32,0:24:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I I was personally\N>> you were you were on the ship but you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.60,0:24:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,almost got blown up yourself but I mean\Nwe you often say I'm so glad I did not
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.36,0:24:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have to take another person's life.\N>> Well that way I would otherwise I would
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.48,0:25:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,spend the rest of my life thinking about\Nthat what that person could have been
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.00,0:25:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,like. that I have the right to take\Ntheir life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.60,0:25:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But out of duty, don't you think that\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.96,0:25:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> that is forgiven because you were doing\Nit out of what had to be done at that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.96,0:25:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,time?\N>> Well, it isn't just a matter of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.36,0:25:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiveness. It's a matter of personal\Nresponsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.72,0:25:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay?\N>> You know, it's like you run over a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.64,0:25:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,pedestrian.\NYou know, you weren't malicious. You
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.64,0:25:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't intend to kill them, but you ran\Nover some little six-year-old in the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.15,0:25:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,intersection. And so that weighs heavily\Non you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.91,0:25:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> That little child, what that child could
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.03,0:25:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,have been\N>> and um
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.20,0:25:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of course all of these occasions bring\Nup, you know, the concept of karma. What
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.40,0:25:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,was that little child's karmic\N>> background? And uh so self forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.55,0:25:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is difficult.\Nunder certain circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.27,0:26:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you cannot see the innocence.\NYou could say that in in one one respect
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.20,0:26:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone is innocent all the time for\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.55,0:26:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you knew divine will, you wouldn't be\Ndoing what you're doing. But you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.24,0:26:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,know divine will. So to what degree are\Nis anyone responsible for their behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.64,0:26:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and under what conditions?\NUnder certain conditions, everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,responsible for everything, and under\Nothers, you're not responsible for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.76,0:26:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.\N>> So, let's say you're driving down the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.44,0:26:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,street and all of a sudden, uh, you\Nhit someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.00,0:26:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> And they and and you killed them. So
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.40,0:26:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically\Nyou were there at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.40,0:26:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> the responsibility.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.03,0:27:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But not necessarily the guilt.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.76,0:27:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The average person would feel guilty. Of\Ncourse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.00,0:27:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> Even if it was the pedestrian's uh
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.03,0:27:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,fault, you would still feel guilty that\Nit was your car that killed them. And
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.67,0:27:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, death has grave consequences.\NBut do you think that but do you think
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.79,0:27:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that um God or the higher\Nuh awareness would know that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.55,0:27:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you could handle that? I mean do you\Nthink that they that God only gives us
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.40,0:27:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,things that we can handle?\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.03,0:27:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't\Nspent any time thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.44,0:27:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> okay\N>> whether God um goes through that kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.44,0:27:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a process with each and every one of us\Nand to me it's more that God sets the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.00,0:27:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,setting in which the things are\N>> matters of dominion
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.36,0:28:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and then within that dominion you have a\Ncertain degree of freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.60,0:28:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> but it's only a matter of degree of\Nfreedom
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.36,0:28:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, none of us are totally free.\N>> You know, I can't decide to be six feet
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.03,0:28:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tall.\NI'm a few inches too short.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.52,0:28:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went in service, I had the I was\Nundersized and underweight, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.03,0:28:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he says, "Uh, he he helped me up\Nthere. He says, "Stand there." He says,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.48,0:28:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Shorty," and I forget how old tall I\Nwas. I don't know, 5 foot seven, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.32,0:28:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, "Stand, you don't quite make\Nit. Just stand on your toes." He says,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.15,0:28:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"Okay, now you make it." He says, "You\Npass."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.39,0:28:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he told me to get on the scale. And\Nuh I didn't pass. So he said, "I want
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.08,0:28:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you to go out and eat bananas and come\Nback in a month." So I went out and I'd
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.52,0:29:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff myself with bananas around the\Nclock.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.48,0:29:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And I came back and and uh and I sit on\Nthe scale and and he put his thumb on
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.20,0:29:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale and he says, "Oh, you just\Nmake it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.27,0:29:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't really tall enough. I didn't\Nweigh enough
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.67,0:29:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wasn't turned really quite\Nphysically strong enough either,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.03,0:29:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wanted to be in the service.\NSo, I was and I uh I'm very grateful for
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.12,0:29:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the opportunity I had\Nand serve the country and be with my
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.39,0:29:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,shipmates.\NAnd uh we we sent Christmas cards to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.55,0:29:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,each other after the World War was over\Nfor many years every year. But each year
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.91,0:29:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of Christmas cards I got\Nwould diminish.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.48,0:29:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I don't get any more Christmas\Ncards. So I'm the last survivor from the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.44,0:30:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ship.\NThe last survivors
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.24,0:30:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,46.\NWell, you often talk about how all of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.32,0:30:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you that served together were um you had\Nthis certain camaraderie,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.15,0:30:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, among you. And I mean, this is\Nyears ago and you still were sending
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.36,0:30:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,cards, you know, every Christmas. So,\N>> Oh, yes. That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.12,0:30:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You never forgot that.\N>> Serving together in that wartime
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.03,0:30:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> uh situation.\N>> Oh, yeah. We were bonded for a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.12,0:30:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we were bonded together for the\Nrest of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.64,0:30:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm the last remaining member of the\Ncrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.67,0:30:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I think you were the youngest,\Nweren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.32,0:30:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I don't remember. I was the smallest,\Nthe lightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.64,0:31:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They called me shorty. And uh\Nyeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.08,0:31:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the smallest member of the crew.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.79,0:31:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So prayer plays a um if we use it daily\Nin our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.91,0:31:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Ndo you think that betters our life?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.52,0:31:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well the the prayer is uh is several\Ndifferent kinds of prayer. One is a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.44,0:31:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,prayer for the general welfare of\Nothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.72,0:31:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's specific prayers for\Nspecific events.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.76,0:31:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's prayers that are more\Npersonal for yourself and your family
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.12,0:31:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and your relatives and you know your\Nmother and your mother-in-law and your
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.72,0:31:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,sister and your daughter and all. Um and\Nthen there's the more general prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.60,0:31:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which I I consider to be reverence.\Nuh to me to be reverent is a style of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.48,0:31:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,praying in which your life becomes the\Nprayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.96,0:32:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Your whole life is one of acknowledgment\Nof the divinity as the source and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.64,0:32:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,value of life.\NIt's not a matter of win or lose. You
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.96,0:32:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,know, people think of\Npraying as winning. You know, you win
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.12,0:32:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with God. If you can pray good enough,\NGod will grant you the wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.91,0:32:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> That's sort of the way a child prays,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.79,0:32:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, dear Lord, please don't let me\Nbe late for class.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.72,0:32:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the kid crimps on the curb and\Nhe says, "But I didn't ask you to push
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.91,0:32:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,me." I love that joke.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.20,0:32:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, sometimes, you know, I mean, I\Nmyself, I have prayed for things that I
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.72,0:32:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,thought that I really needed or wanted\Nor wanted to happen or whatever. And
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.48,0:32:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,yet, when it didn't happen, I saw uh I\Nit was a different picture and it was
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.51,0:33:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the way it was better that my that my\Nprayer wasn't answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.91,0:33:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, I've had that happen.\N>> Yes. to where you you think, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.32,0:33:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, I really want to want this this to\Nhappen. This is just got to happen for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.76,0:33:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,me. And yet, when that prayer isn't\Nanswered, it's much better the way it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.51,0:33:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,turned out.\N>> That's the way it reveals itself, the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.84,0:33:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,truth behind it.\N>> So, you know, it just amazes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.51,0:33:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's very nice that we uh have\Nsufficient humility that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.60,0:33:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we can acknowledge the gift whether we\Nit's granted or not granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.96,0:33:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Either way there's a gift\Nfor it not to be granted opens up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.91,0:33:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,certain doorways and for it to be\Ngranted opens up other doorways.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.60,0:34:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So in a way you might say you always win\Nwith prayer. You either get it or you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.48,0:34:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,don't. And either way, it's beneficial.\N>> You pray for a million dollars and you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.24,0:34:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't get it. You say, "Well, God felt\Nthat that would have been harmful to my
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.48,0:34:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,life."\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.24,0:34:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And you you pray for a million dollars\Nand you get it. You say, "God had
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.96,0:34:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,confidence in my ability to to handle\Nthis for the good of others." Because
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.44,0:34:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,now the million dollars gives you an\Nobligation to be helpful to others with
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.63,0:34:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that million dollars.\N>> Yeah. We talked about stewardship.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.39,0:34:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> The stewardship that is involved in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.63,0:34:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,serving others.\N>> You never really own anything or nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.63,0:34:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is really yours. You're you're only the\Nsteward of it for a certain period of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.32,0:34:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,time\N>> and then it passes on to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.07,0:34:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I've always had that, you know, I\Nlike antiques.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.87,0:35:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uhu.\NSo, I've always had it in mind that I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.96,0:35:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just a keeper of those for that time in\Nmy life and then it passes on to someone
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.80,0:35:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,else because some of the antiques are\Nhundreds of years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.52,0:35:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's right.\N>> So, it just, you know, I enjoy it from
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.16,0:35:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that time in my life and then it goes on\Nto someone else who's going to enjoy it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.40,0:35:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> willing to share the beauty of it and\Nthe treasure of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.48,0:35:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> the value of it. Mhm.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.16,0:35:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, you know, when you look at it from\Nthat point of view, it's the same with
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.20,0:35:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,everything in your life basically that\Neverything can be looked at like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.35,0:35:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's what makes your life turns your\Nlife into a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.16,0:35:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm. where you see everything as a gift\Nor a lesson
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.72,0:35:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and you see the benefit that it\Nbrings to yourself and to others and you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.40,0:35:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,pray to be helpful to the life of those\Nyou love.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.76,0:36:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. So if speaking that we're talking\Nabout lottery and everything, if we
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.28,0:36:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to bring uh prosperity into our\Nlives,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.80,0:36:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I have found that the quickest way that\Nhappens to me is when I
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.68,0:36:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,try and do good for others in their\Nlife,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.83,0:36:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> then I'm rewarded not only for that, but\Nfrom my own aspects. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.64,0:36:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionally,\Num, spiritually, it it does so much more
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.52,0:36:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to give to others than it does\Nto,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.56,0:36:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,um,\Njust want. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.48,0:36:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And want.\N>> So, we get we get uh by giving.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.16,0:36:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, this day and age, everybody's, you\Nknow, financially, everybody's com, you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.64,0:36:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,know, talking about this. So that's why\NI'm bringing this up
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.52,0:36:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and they are financially.\N>> Oh yeah, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.56,0:37:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> about it.\NAll the people on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.83,0:37:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, I see.\N>> Where Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.92,0:37:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> well, it's because it's the holidays are\N>> right
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.11,0:37:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> close by. And that always brings up the\Nwhole subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.40,0:37:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right? for greater intensity. Prayer and\Ndevotion and church and religion and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.56,0:37:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,holiness. All these aspects\Num come up for reinforcement and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.00,0:37:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,re-examination with every holiday.\N>> Well, Thanksgiving is coming up pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.24,0:37:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly, is it not?\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.00,0:37:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> So, if we were to give, what would you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.07,0:37:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you say we should do as a\Nthanksgiving prayer? What should we do
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.28,0:37:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to be to let God know that we're\Nthankful for what we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.07,0:37:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Just pray up a storm.\N>> Rattle the dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.35,0:37:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Rattle the dishes.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.32,0:38:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the way we live our life is is uh\Ndepends on how we view divinity. If
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.44,0:38:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity is ever present,\Nthis lovingness is a field in which we
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.64,0:38:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,operate and thrive.\NSo this lovingness to me, God is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.92,0:38:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness. Lovingness\Nand um
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.68,0:38:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the propensity for love to go to love.\NThe propensity is for love to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.32,0:38:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,love.\NWe recently had a lecture on love,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.72,0:38:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't we? It went on love. Yes. And it\Nhad to do with the propensity of love to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.92,0:38:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,go to love.\NSo, it's kind of weird that here we have
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.72,0:38:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this Thanksgiving holiday, you know,\Nthat involves bounty, you know, because
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.44,0:38:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we celebrate.\N>> We have, you know, the harvest basically
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.83,0:39:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is how it all started. But, um, we're\Nthankful for
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.59,0:39:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,our family, friends,\Num,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.80,0:39:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the food that we eat. Um, so we, you\Nknow, our holidays should, the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.24,0:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanksgiving holiday is a chance to\Nreally be thankful for the gifts that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.48,0:39:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have been granted us.\N>> We're surrounded by gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.80,0:39:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Mhm. The fact that we are still alive. I
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.80,0:39:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Well, thank you, God, that I'm\Nstill alive."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.07,0:39:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, and I\Ncan you, you know, devote my life to the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.59,0:39:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,usefulness to others.\N>> So, that gives it some value.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.80,0:39:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because just having things doesn't\Nincrease value.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.96,0:39:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,U\Nit increases fun and pleasure, but it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.88,0:39:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really increase value.\N>> And it could be that certain lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.92,0:40:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you spend more lifetimes in service,\Nwould you say, to others rather than um
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.35,0:40:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. I think if you go into the\Nhistorical background of many people,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.04,0:40:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find uh a certain pattern to\Ntheir
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.32,0:40:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> recurrent recurrent emergence another\Nhuman life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.56,0:40:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to be of service or to make up for\Nhaving not been of service.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.48,0:40:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo if you were to sum everything up as
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.48,0:40:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,um live your life like a prayer, what\Nmessage would you give us?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.00,0:40:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To be grateful for the opportunity for\Nyour own existence. I always say dear
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.11,0:40:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,God I'm very grateful that I exist\Nand I consider this a gift which I
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.56,0:40:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,treasure and I will try to use this gift\Nto the best of my ability
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.00,0:40:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to spread that love to and gratitude to\Nothers. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.59,0:41:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way I express my gratitude to God\Nis by being loving towards others to the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.83,0:41:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest extent I could do so\N>> even when they pull out in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.88,0:41:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's just a childish annoyance\Nthat somebody's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.64,0:41:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> has gotten in your way. It's a little\Nscary. That's right. As you're racing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.72,0:41:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,down the highway, suddenly a car pulls\Nout
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.07,0:41:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,from the side of the road right in front\Nof you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.07,0:41:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It's just very hard to to say take what\Nyou're saying and put it into every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.80,0:41:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, it's an it's an attitude. And\Nbecause it's an attitude, it prevails
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.76,0:41:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and covers all the conditions.\NSo if a car is going too slow,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.83,0:41:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you have one kind of response. If the\Ncar is pulling out too fast, you have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.44,0:41:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,another response.\NBut all of them are being governed by
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.92,0:42:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your great gratitude\Nthat you have the opportunity to save
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.56,0:42:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,people's lives to serve other people and\Nto be alive for the benefit of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.28,0:42:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and others. Amen. Mhm.\N>> So live your life like a prayer every
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.00,0:42:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,day and in every way\N>> to be grateful for your own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.31,0:42:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to share your appreciation to God\Nthat you exist
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.56,0:42:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the opportunity to express your love\Ntowards others
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.35,0:42:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,uh is a gift from God. And I give thanks\Nto thee, oh Lord, for the gift of being
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.80,0:42:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,able to be here with you right now and\Nand record this event.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.88,0:42:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, dear Lord, for the chance to\Nrecord this event. And after you and I
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.56,0:42:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are long gone, that this recording will\Nstill be available if anybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.28,0:42:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,interested.\NWay back in the olden times
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.16,0:43:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when old Doc Hawkins and old Susan\NHawkins
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.76,0:43:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were still kicking around and alive, you\Nknow, way way back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.64,0:43:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be old, old old folks before you\Nknow it. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.35,0:43:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right. Thank you.
